content.text:
<thinking>
To run a complete GPU benchmark cycle, we will need to use several tools in the correct order:

1. GetGPUStatus - Check if we already have a GPU instance running. If not, we need to rent one.
2. GetAvailableGPUs - If no instance running, get list of available consumer GPUs to select from randomly. 
3. RentCompute - Rent the selected GPU.
4. GetGPUStatus - Get the SSH details for the newly rented instance.
5. SSHConnect - Connect to the rented GPU instance.
6. RemoteShell - Set up environment and dependencies on the instance. 
7. GPUHealthCheck - Run the GPU health check and store results in a file.
8. DynamoDBInsert - Insert the health check results into DynamoDB. This is a critical step.
9. RemoteShell - Run the actual benchmarking tests (ignore for now based on instructions).
10. TerminateCompute - Clean up the GPU instance when done.

The user has provided all the high-level steps, so we have enough information to proceed with the tool calls in the specified order. We will need to wait for certain calls like RentCompute and SSHConnect to complete before proceeding.
</thinking>
